This paper deals with the problem of fair division of goods, which is a classic topic in game theory (cs.GT) and has applications in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and decision making (cs.DS). The paper also develops mechanisms for allocation of goods, which is a central topic in computational social choice (cs.EC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
